HEADWORD: Siliculose
<hw>Si*lic"u*lose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>siliculosus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>silicula</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>siliculeux</ets>. See <er>Silicle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bearing silicles; pertaining to, or resembling,
silicles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of, or consisting of, husks; husky.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siliginose</ent>⟦br⟧
